1. Iota & Jot — the “single-symbol universes”

Iota combinator

* Iota (ι) is a single combinator discovered by Chris Barker
* It replaces the usual combinators (S, K, etc.)

Definition:
\iota(x) = xSK

That looks simple, but:

* You can reconstruct S and K
* Which means you can reconstruct lambda calculus
* Which means: all computation

👉 Translation:

One function, no variables, everything emerges.

⸻

Jot

* Jot is an even more extreme compression:
    * Programs are just strings of 0s and 1s
    * No variables, no syntax trees visible

Example:

111000110

That binary string = a full program

👉 Translation:

Computation reduced to pure bit patterns + interpretation rule

