Definition

\mathcal{H}(S, F) = \text{Update}(S, \hat{S}_{future}(F))

Where:

* S = current state
* F = future attractor hypothesis
* \hat{S}_{future} = predicted state under F
* Update = minimal adjustment toward predicted trajectory

⸻

Expanded form

\mathcal{H}(S, F) =
S + \alpha \cdot (\hat{S}_{F} - S) \cdot w

* \alpha = step size (agency / commitment)
* w = confidence weighting

⸻

Interpretation

* Predict a future
* Compare to current
* Move slightly toward it
* Repeat

